HEADWORD: Wilfley table
<hw>Wil"fley ta`ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Ore Dressing)</fld> <def>An
inclined percussion table, usually with longitudinal grooves in its
surface, agitated by side blows at right angles to the flow of the pulp;
-- so called after the inventor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

